				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\oint {\vec H\,d\vec l\, = \,} \int\limits_1 {\vec H\,d\vec l\, + \,} \int\limits_2 {\vec H\,d\vec l\, + \,} \int\limits_3 {\vec H\,d\vec l\, + \,} \int\limits_4 {\vec H\,d\vec l\,} = \,0$$\end{document}Fig. 3.7
The shape of the magnetic field lines in the gap between the pole pieces results in a focusing effect on the particles being accelerated

